              <text><![CDATA[Good. You got it right. 

Cargo tanks are usually located in sets of three and they are numbered from forward towards the aft. For example, the foremost three tanks are called 1P, 1C  and 1S (“one port”, “one centre”,  “one starboard”). Wing tanks are on the port and starboard sides of the ship. Centre tanks are between the wing tanks. 
New tankers have a double hull. It protects against the spillage of hazardous cargo in the event of grounding or collision. Hazardous cargo is any cargo which may cause harm to humans, animals or the environment. Please continue with NEXT.

 ]]></text>
